+# Solution for Issue: Cosmos: support top-level Any()
+
+## Root Cause
+
+Cosmos DB does not support uncorrelated subqueries. The `EXISTS(SELECT 1 FROM root c WHERE ...)` pattern only works when the subquery source is an array property on the current document — it cannot reference a top-level container scan. When `Any()` was used at the top level of a query (e.g., `context.Customers.Any()`), EF Core generated an `EXISTS` subquery referencing `root c`, which is an uncorrelated reference that Cosmos DB rejects with a `BadRequest` error.
+
+## Change Description
+
+Modified `TranslateAny` in `CosmosQueryableMethodTranslatingExpressionVisitor` to detect when it is translating a top-level (non-subquery) `Any()` call and use a different strategy:
+
+Instead of wrapping the source in `EXISTS(SELECT 1 ...)`, the fix:
+1. Clears orderings (irrelevant for existence check) when no prior OFFSET/LIMIT is present.
+2. Applies `LIMIT 1` to stop scanning after the first matching document.
+3. Replaces the projection with a constant `true` value (`SELECT VALUE true`).
+4. Returns with `ResultCardinality.SingleOrDefault` so that when no rows are returned (no matching documents), the result is the default value of `bool` (`false`).
+
+The result is a query of the form:
+```sql
+SELECT VALUE true
+FROM root c
+WHERE <predicates>
+OFFSET 0 LIMIT 1
+```
+
+If the source already has an existing `LIMIT` applied (e.g., `.Take(10).Any()`), the fix falls back to a translation failure because subquery pushdown is not supported in Cosmos DB. This is a better outcome than the previous behavior which generated a syntactically invalid query that failed at runtime.
+
+The existing `EXISTS`-based path is preserved for the subquery context (`_subquery = true`), where `Any()` inside a correlated subquery (e.g., over a JSON array property) still works correctly.
+
+## Files Edited
+
+- `src/EFCore.Cosmos/Query/Internal/CosmosQueryableMethodTranslatingExpressionVisitor.cs` — main fix in `TranslateAny`
+- `test/EFCore.Cosmos.FunctionalTests/Query/NorthwindMiscellaneousQueryCosmosTest.cs` — updated `Any_simple`, `Any_predicate`, `OrderBy_ThenBy_Any`, `Skip_Take_Any` test expectations
+- `test/EFCore.Cosmos.FunctionalTests/Query/NorthwindAggregateOperatorsQueryCosmosTest.cs` — updated `Contains_top_level`, `Contains_over_entityType_with_null_should_rewrite_to_false` test expectations
